  "description": "This dataset comprises MEG phantom recordings used to evaluate and compare deep brain stimulation (DBS) artifact rejection methods. The study systematically assesses the performance of various artifact rejection techniques applied to MEG data contaminated with DBS-related artifacts, providing a standardized benchmark for validating preprocessing approaches in DBS-MEG studies.",
  "methods_description": "MEG phantom recordings were acquired using a CTF system. Stimulation reference signals were captured via EEG001, movement triggers via UPPT001, and dipole activity via HADC006. The dataset includes measurements designed to evaluate multiple DBS artifact rejection methods.",
